        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No record of the substance of this meeting has been found. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_EA1"
                        >Eden</persName>, who were both quartered on board H. M. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Sirius</hi> in Grand Harbor, Malta, went ashore in the early
                    part of the morning and took a walk, during the course of which, it seems, they
                    “discussed some of the problems to be raised at Yalta”. This information is
                    taken from <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName>, <ref
                        target="#pg_60">pp. 60</ref>, <ref target="#pg_62">62</ref>, <ref
                        target="#pg_63">63</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
